-- This deck tests usage of NNC in combination with EDITNNC for an overlaping
-- value. The deck has only two active cells [1,1,1] and [2,1,2], i.e., only
-- one TRANNNC is internally generated with value 0.10000000E+01 (i.e., using
-- the permeability and geometry information from the cells), which is then
-- set to 0 using EDITNNC 1 1 1 2 1 2 0. However, by using NNC, one can set
-- a desired value, in this case 6666 (NNC 1 1 1 2 1 2 6666), which internally
-- in the simulator is used and written to the INIT (0.66660000E+04). In sum,
-- this is useful to overwritte NNCs computed internally in the simulator.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
RUNSPEC
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
DIMENS 
2 1 2 /

CO2STORE
GAS
WATER

EQLDIMS
/

TABDIMS
/

WELLDIMS
/

UNIFOUT
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
GRID
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
INIT

COORD
     0   0 0      0   0 2E3
 2.5E3   0 0  2.5E3   0 2E3
   5E3   0 0    5E3   0 2E3
     0 1E3 0      0 1E3 2E3
 2.5E3 1E3 0  2.5E3 1E3 2E3
   5E3 1E3 0    5E3 1E3 2E3 /

ZCORN
2*0    2*5E2    2*0 2*5E2
2*10E2 2*5E2 2*10E2 2*5E2
2*10E2 2*5E2 2*10E2 2*5E2
8*10E2 /

PORO
4*0.1 /

PERMX
4*0.58637152 /

COPY
PERMX PERMY /
PERMX PERMZ /
/

NNC
1 1 1 2 1 2 6666 /
/
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
EDIT
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
EDITNNC
1 1 1 2 1 2 0 /
/
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
PROPS
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
SGWFN
0 0 1 0
1 1 0 0 /
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
SOLUTION
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
RPTRST
BASIC=2 /

EQUIL
0 200 0 0 0 0 1 1 0 /
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
SUMMARY
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
BPR
2 1 2 /
/
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
SCHEDULE
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
RPTRST
BASIC=2 /

SOURCE
1 1 1 WATER 1E8 /
/

TSTEP
1 /
